In the terminal, run the following command to install the node package named mongoose for connnecting to MongoDB server.
npm install mongoose@8.0.3
To provide API end points, we need a running server. Express is a Node.js web application framework that allows you to host services. Run the following command to install express.
npm install express
To process the input sent to the API end point, you need to install the package body-parser which will be used a middleware. Run the following command to install the package.
npm install body-parser
To test the API endpoints from POSTMAN, you need to install the package cors which will be used as middleware. Run the following command to install the package.